ALIGN="center" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 BGCOLOR=white WIDTH="100%"> <TR> <TD><p><em>Note on updates to the Timetable -- It is important to check the Timetable, rather than the ORC to confirm the latest information about a course, including the meeting time, instructor, and distributive and/or world culture designation associated with a course. </em></p></TD> </TR> <TR> <TD>&nbsp;</TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><p><em>The distributive column on the Timetable is important since it contains the most up-to-date information on the distributive and/or world culture designation for the course. In some cases, the instructor has submitted a request to the Committee on Instruction for a change or addition in the distributive or world culture designation for a course since the ORC was published. </em></p></TD> </TR> <TR> <TD>&nbsp;</TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><p><em>Click on the subject code link below to view ORC(Organization, Regulation and Course) information for that subject. </em></p></TD> </TR> <TR> <TD>&nbsp;</TD> </TR> <TR> <TD><p><em>To view textbook requirements information as entered by the department/program at the time of course election, click on the course
